1
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:45,950
[THE DEVIL BETWEEN US]

2
00:01:45,970 --> 00:01:49,020
[Episode 8]

3
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:37,940
What are you doing?

4
00:02:39,110 --> 00:02:40,370
It's for your own good.

5
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:42,000
Whatever you want to ask,

6
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,000
we'll talk later.

7
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,800
We'll take another route back later.

8
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:46,329
Go.

9
00:02:48,290 --> 00:02:48,720
Hurry.

10
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,350
The police will be here soon.

11
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:24,650
Drive your own car!

12
00:04:17,269 --> 00:04:18,399
Split up and search!

13
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,600
Get out of the car.

14
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,829
Here!

15
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:22,240
Here!

16
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:22,920
Hurry.

17
00:04:24,290 --> 00:04:25,490
Don't fall asleep!

18
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:27,600
Is the ambulance here yet?

19
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,360
Almost.

20
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,080
Where is Ding Lai?

21
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:30,760
He ran away.

22
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:32,040
You take a car, I'll take another.

23
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:32,760
We have to search outside.

24
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:33,230
Okay.

25
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:33,950
Okay, I'll keep an eye on the ambulance.

26
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:34,480
Let's go!

27
00:04:37,430 --> 00:04:38,690
The ambulance is here.

28
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:40,600
We're going after Ding Lai now.

29
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,040
Here!

30
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:41,680
Over here!

31
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,240
Hurry up!

32
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:44,800
Follow me!

33
00:04:45,050 --> 00:04:45,680
Hurry up.

34
00:04:54,540 --> 00:04:55,800
You're off work early.

35
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:06,870
Dad!

36
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:09,750
Xiaoyu,

37
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:10,700
Dad is back.

38
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:12,020
You can come out now.

39
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:28,900
Xiaoyu.

40
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:57,670
Stop!

41
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,160
He's not breathing anymore.

42
00:08:58,730 --> 00:08:59,640
What are you doing?

43
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,440
Get in the car.

44
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,320
From now on,

45
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:22,410
whatever we do,

46
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,300
we have to be extremely careful.

47
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,360
Remember this—

48
00:09:26,650 --> 00:09:28,340
if the police find out,

49
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,130
I'll take the fall for everything.

50
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:33,050
I'll tell them

51
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:34,720
I killed Ding Lai

52
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:36,150
out of jealousy

53
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:37,150
and revenge.

54
00:09:38,030 --> 00:09:39,630
It has nothing to do with you.

55
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:43,710
This is all we can do.

56
00:09:45,030 --> 00:09:45,840
Leave the rest

57
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,480
to fate.

58
00:09:57,970 --> 00:09:59,330
Since when did you know?

59
00:10:02,180 --> 00:10:03,780
Where is the phone I gave you?

60
00:10:15,730 --> 00:10:17,590
I installed a mini-program in it.

61
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:25,460
I don't even want to talk about
Cheng Xiaodong.

62
00:10:25,460 --> 00:10:25,860
I'm telling you,

63
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:27,490
he's completely finished now—

64
00:10:27,490 --> 00:10:28,820
obsessed with fishing.

65
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:30,760
And it's not enough for him

66
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:33,110
to go to a regular fishing spot anymore;

67
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:34,680
he even rents fishing boats.

68
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,420
I'm definitely

69
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:36,450
getting a divorce.

70
00:10:36,450 --> 00:10:37,690
Didn't you use to say

71
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:39,330
it's good for a man to have a hobby?

72
00:10:39,330 --> 00:10:41,530
She actually used to
support Cheng Xiaodong's fishing.

73
00:10:41,530 --> 00:10:43,670
I only said that before to save his face.

74
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:44,550
Let me tell you—

75
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:46,420
when a successful man goes fishing,

76
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:47,510
it's a hobby;

77
00:10:47,550 --> 00:10:48,860
when a man with no career does it,

78
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:50,590
it's just aimless indulgence.

79
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:52,390
With a narcotics officer dead,

80
00:10:52,460 --> 00:10:53,620
going back to Haizhou to make money again

81
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,790
is impossible now.

82
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:56,380
The best way

83
00:10:56,410 --> 00:10:57,570
is to recruit Daquan

84
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:01,040
and use his distribution network
to make some quick cash.

85
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:03,310
I'll send you a location later.

86
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:05,170
Bring the money and meet me there.

87
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:06,440
Xiaoya,

88
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:08,670
give me a hug.

89
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:14,780
Come on.

90
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:15,540
Turn around.

91
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:19,340
If I get arrested

92
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,910
or die in some accident,

93
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,740
the police will find you

94
00:11:22,740 --> 00:11:23,710
through this photo.

95
00:11:23,710 --> 00:11:25,170
You won't get away either.

96
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,500
So what, do you want to die

97
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:30,120
and drag someone down with you?

98
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:42,310
You've been eavesdropping on me
this whole time?

99
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:43,310
Are you sick?

100
00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:47,460
I just wanted to help you.

101
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:54,670
So you knew everything

102
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:56,000
I've been doing lately.

103
00:11:57,620 --> 00:11:59,420
You knew Ding Lai was at my place,

104
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,790
you knew who he was,

105
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:04,860
but you never let it show.

106
00:12:07,340 --> 00:12:08,790
Didn't I ask you before

107
00:12:09,310 --> 00:12:10,710
if there was another man?

108
00:12:11,310 --> 00:12:12,370
You didn't answer.

109
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,340
So I figured you didn't want to tell me.

110
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:17,850
I decided to pretend I didn't know.

111
00:12:17,850 --> 00:12:18,560
It's okay.

112
00:12:19,020 --> 00:12:19,780
I don't care.

113
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:21,750
As long as you're happy,

114
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:23,190
I'm fine with anything.

115
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:24,420
Are you insane?

116
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,340
Yes.

117
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:27,630
If loving you is a sickness,

118
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:30,590
then I have a terminal illness.

119
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,030
Cheng Xiaodong,

120
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:38,080
I want to jump out of the car.

121
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:39,600
I'm clumsy with words.

122
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,820
I'm not a smooth talker like Ding Lai.

123
00:12:44,260 --> 00:12:45,790
But my hands aren't clumsy.

124
00:12:48,580 --> 00:12:51,440
I never thought
killing someone could be this easy.

125
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:07,740
Delete whatever you installed

126
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:08,550
on my phone.

127
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,080
Forget it.

128
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:14,790
I'll just switch phones.

129
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:19,800
If there's anything else
you're hiding from me,

130
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:20,730
tell me all of it.

131
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:25,950
Do you remember

132
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:27,340
how we first met?

133
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:29,790
At a KTV,

134
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:31,790
my friend got drunk

135
00:13:31,930 --> 00:13:33,100
and walked into the wrong room.

136
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,190
He argued with your colleagues,

137
00:13:36,070 --> 00:13:37,670
and I went over to apologize.

138
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:39,820
That's how we met.

139
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:41,270
Do you remember?

140
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:43,650
Yes.

141
00:13:45,810 --> 00:13:47,290
I arranged all of that.

142
00:13:48,710 --> 00:13:50,070
My friend wasn't drunk,

143
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:52,810
and I already knew your colleagues
back then.

144
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,190
Why me?

145
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:23,440
At the time my startup had failed.

146
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:25,520
I couldn't take it,

147
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:27,920
so I was going to jump into the sea.

148
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:29,980
"Smooth traffic on your way home,

149
00:14:29,980 --> 00:14:31,100
an easy life always."

150
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,950
This is Nuanfeng County People's Radio,

151
00:14:32,950 --> 00:14:34,280
the Voice of Nuanhai program.

152
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:35,440
I am your friend,

153
00:14:35,790 --> 00:14:36,390
Xiaoya.

154
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:39,420
Whether you're on your way home from work

155
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,460
or getting dinner ready at home,

156
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:44,610
I hope you can set aside
the burdens of a long day

157
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,400
and embrace the beautiful evening ahead.

158
00:14:48,190 --> 00:14:49,020
Yesterday,

159
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,440
a listener who goes by CXD

160
00:14:51,470 --> 00:14:53,120
left a message on our forum.

161
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,280
He said

162
00:14:54,310 --> 00:14:56,370
that after graduating from college,

163
00:14:56,490 --> 00:14:59,090
he used his family's money
to start a business,

164
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,430
but it failed,

165
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:03,310
and now he feels like
there's no hope for the future.

166
00:15:03,310 --> 00:15:04,070
Actually,

167
00:15:04,390 --> 00:15:05,510
in the journey of life,

168
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:07,750
it's only natural to hit low points.

169
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:08,820
So

170
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:09,670
I

171
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:12,070
would like to send this friend

172
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:13,390
a little encouragement.

173
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:15,790
Life is about climbing

174
00:15:15,820 --> 00:15:17,630
one hill after another.

175
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:20,750
There's no valley you can't walk out of.

176
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,310
This next song is for you.

177
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:24,390
I hope you'll

178
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:26,390
try to love a little more,

179
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:28,070
wait a little longer,

180
00:15:28,890 --> 00:15:30,910
and keep traveling on through life—

181
00:15:31,150 --> 00:15:31,940
just for

182
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:34,170
the people who warm your heart.

183
00:15:34,170 --> 00:15:36,390
♪ For the direction my heart longs for ♪

184
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:41,060
♪ A simple, modest dream ♪

185
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,360
♪ Now holding on to freedom ♪

186
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:45,870
♪ Carrying a heart that seeks its ideals ♪

187
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:48,040
♪ One life, one shining pursuit ♪

188
00:15:48,060 --> 00:15:49,790
♪ Faith will never fade ♪

189
00:15:49,810 --> 00:15:51,720
♪ With you and me together ♪

190
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:53,470
♪ Joining forces to explore ♪

191
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:56,490
♪ Through our unrestrained years ahead ♪

192
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:58,470
♪ One day, with smiles ♪

193
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:01,050
♪ We'll pause within the evening sky's view ♪

194
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:03,470
♪ No matter how far the horizon,
just run with all your strength ♪

195
00:16:03,490 --> 00:16:04,720
♪ No matter how far, no regrets ♪

196
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:06,470
♪ The dreams of our youth ♪

197
00:16:06,490 --> 00:16:08,480
♪ Will last forever ♪

198
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:13,240
♪ Someday we'll meet at a crossroads ♪

199
00:16:14,070 --> 00:16:23,470
♪ Someday we'll meet at a crossroads ♪

200
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:56,210
I always knew you were a deep thinker,

201
00:16:58,250 --> 00:16:59,380
but I never imagined

202
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:04,119
you'd hide everything

203
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,540
this deeply.

204
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:13,589
When I go night fishing,

205
00:17:14,869 --> 00:17:16,599
I run into all kinds of anglers.

206
00:17:19,089 --> 00:17:20,690
I divide them into two types —

207
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:22,839
those who

208
00:17:24,660 --> 00:17:27,119
sit there all night
thinking about nothing,

209
00:17:28,349 --> 00:17:29,220
and those

210
00:17:30,660 --> 00:17:32,520
who sit there thinking all night.

211
00:17:34,740 --> 00:17:35,870
I'm the latter.

212
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:43,030
I don't understand
all this nonsense you're saying.

213
00:17:44,910 --> 00:17:46,640
I just want to ask you one thing—

214
00:17:46,930 --> 00:17:48,260
will you always help me?

215
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:48,960
Yes.

216
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:51,740
What do you want?

217
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,520
Do you want to marry me again?

218
00:18:02,740 --> 00:18:04,700
That depends on
whether you really want to.

219
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:05,840
As long as you are happy,

220
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:06,840
anything is fine.

221
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:14,870
If I say I don't want to,

222
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:19,070
you won't go crazy right now, will you?

223
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:20,460
No.

224
00:18:22,850 --> 00:18:23,960
Before I did this,

225
00:18:24,550 --> 00:18:27,280
I was already mentally
prepared for everything.

226
00:18:31,390 --> 00:18:33,520
You really don't have any conditions?

227
00:18:39,970 --> 00:18:40,530
I do.

228
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:46,710
Rest your head on my lap.

229
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:47,670
What?

230
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:50,390
Rest your head on my lap.

231
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:52,860
I like the way you lie on my lap

232
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:54,060
watching TV.

233
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:37,920
Too bad…

234
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:40,670
There isn't a single star

235
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:41,950
in the sky tonight.

236
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:26,210
It's really my first time
coming to the riverside late at night.

237
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:29,160
Will you still give me

238
00:20:29,380 --> 00:20:31,110
12,000 yuan a month from now on?

239
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:33,410
from now on?

240
00:20:35,370 --> 00:20:36,030
What?

241
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:40,040
I mean the 12,000 yuan a month.

242
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:41,420
Cheng Ken,

243
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,830
are you out of your mind?

244
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:46,830
That money was for the position,

245
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,320
not for you.

246
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,830
You embezzled over 2,000,000 yuan

247
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:54,780
and I did nothing.

248
00:20:54,780 --> 00:20:56,130
Now I'm taking all the blame.

249
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:56,980
I lost my job

250
00:20:56,980 --> 00:20:57,700
because of you.

251
00:20:57,700 --> 00:20:58,630
You caused this.

252
00:20:59,080 --> 00:21:00,610
Give me an explanation now!

253
00:21:09,430 --> 00:21:10,290
I'm sorry, I...

254
00:21:10,950 --> 00:21:12,280
Give me an explanation.

255
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:15,440
Cheng Ken,

256
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:18,300
when I got into your car just now,

257
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:20,300
we were outside the factory, right?

258
00:21:22,090 --> 00:21:23,350
But that day you told me

259
00:21:24,070 --> 00:21:26,670
when you got into my car,
it was inside the factory—

260
00:21:26,670 --> 00:21:28,020
where there are cameras.

261
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:29,500
So if you drown,

262
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,700
I'd have to go down with you, wouldn't I?

263
00:21:31,980 --> 00:21:34,980
There aren't any cameras
outside the factory, right?

264
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,350
What's wrong?

265
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:38,130
What's wrong?

266
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,260
You know what I mean.

267
00:21:39,890 --> 00:21:40,820
What's wrong?

268
00:21:42,780 --> 00:21:45,570
Keep messing with me
and I'll wipe out your whole family.

269
00:21:45,570 --> 00:21:47,230
You've got a daughter, right?

270
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,440
Can she swim?

271
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,260
This place is a dump—
it's the middle of the night

272
00:21:59,260 --> 00:22:00,660
and I can't even get a cab.

273
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:03,010
I'm driving your car away.

274
00:22:03,010 --> 00:22:04,010
Come get it from me

275
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:05,990
at the factory gate tomorrow.

276
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:33,060
Dad,

277
00:23:35,300 --> 00:23:35,910
what's wrong with you?

278
00:23:35,910 --> 00:23:36,910
I'm fine.

279
00:23:36,910 --> 00:23:37,630
I'm really fine.

280
00:23:37,630 --> 00:23:38,780
You won't believe
what I'm about to tell you.

281
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:39,670
Just now on my way back,

282
00:23:39,670 --> 00:23:40,800
I saw a big white fish

283
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,230
in the river.

284
00:23:43,070 --> 00:23:44,200
-How big?
-Very big.

285
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:45,360
This big.

286
00:23:45,390 --> 00:23:46,190
This big?

287
00:23:46,810 --> 00:23:47,400
This big!

288
00:23:47,430 --> 00:23:48,080
This big.

289
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:49,060
It's white.

290
00:23:49,260 --> 00:23:49,980
White?

291
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:51,550
It was white like this.

292
00:23:51,550 --> 00:23:52,800
Even whiter than this.

293
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:53,740
It was glowing.

294
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:54,630
Glowing?

295
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:55,870
Its scales were glowing.

296
00:23:55,870 --> 00:23:56,910
Is it this big?

297
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:57,990
It was bigger than this.

298
00:23:57,990 --> 00:23:59,340
And it had a big tail.

299
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,870
Its tail was even bigger than this.

300
00:24:00,870 --> 00:24:02,300
Just imagine how big the fish was.

301
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:03,540
It was swinging its big tail

302
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:04,300
right there in the river.

303
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:06,170
It was just circling and circling.

304
00:24:06,170 --> 00:24:06,840
Really?

305
00:24:06,870 --> 00:24:07,970
I wanted to catch it.

306
00:24:07,970 --> 00:24:09,300
So I jumped into the water

307
00:24:09,300 --> 00:24:10,630
and started chasing it.

308
00:24:11,460 --> 00:24:12,920
But I couldn't catch up no matter what.

309
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:13,850
It was too fast.

310
00:24:13,950 --> 00:24:15,060
That big tail

311
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:16,630
kept slapping the water—

312
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:18,220
splash, splash—and jumping up like this.

313
00:24:18,220 --> 00:24:19,080
Then I realized

314
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:21,110
there were little fish beside it too.

315
00:24:21,110 --> 00:24:22,600
-Little fish?
-How many?

316
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:24,760
About four or five.

317
00:24:25,190 --> 00:24:25,630
They were also

318
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:26,390
white.

319
00:24:26,390 --> 00:24:27,630
And there were red ones too.

320
00:24:27,630 --> 00:24:28,550
They were glowing too.

321
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,530
Was it that big?

322
00:24:29,550 --> 00:24:30,630
It was bigger than this.

323
00:24:30,630 --> 00:24:31,260
Bigger than this?

324
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:32,100
They were along...

325
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:33,700
Then the big fish swam ahead,

326
00:24:33,730 --> 00:24:35,010
and the little fish

327
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:36,850
were jumping on its back.

328
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:38,050
I want to see them too.

329
00:24:38,590 --> 00:24:39,260
They swam away.

330
00:24:39,260 --> 00:24:40,350
I couldn't catch up.

331
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:41,590
How about another day?

332
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:43,420
Dad will take you to see it once a week.

333
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:44,070
Really?

334
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:45,700
I can't guarantee when we'll see them,

335
00:24:45,700 --> 00:24:47,390
but we'll definitely go look once a week.

336
00:24:47,390 --> 00:24:49,120
We'll wait there that night for them.

337
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,650
We'll definitely see them.

338
00:24:53,790 --> 00:24:54,650
Keep watching.

339
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,010
I'm going to wash up.

340
00:26:07,390 --> 00:26:09,160
I wish everyone perseverance to the end

341
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:10,660
and assets worth over 100 million.

342
00:26:10,660 --> 00:26:11,750
Good!

343
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:17,350
Don't go inside.

344
00:26:17,350 --> 00:26:18,190
Come here.

345
00:26:19,270 --> 00:26:19,980
Stand properly.

346
00:26:19,980 --> 00:26:21,720
Don't think this is over.

347
00:26:21,750 --> 00:26:22,700
Do you know

348
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,120
what you did wrong today?

349
00:26:24,730 --> 00:26:26,600
Our parents were called in again.

350
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:40,650
The hallucinogen you took

351
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:42,480
is extremely potent.

352
00:26:42,910 --> 00:26:46,040
It can alter your personality
on a psychological level.

353
00:26:46,410 --> 00:26:47,750
What's even more frightening

354
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:49,750
is that your brain is being deceived

355
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:51,910
and you won't even notice the change,

356
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:54,910
because it reshapes
your perception itself.

357
00:26:55,170 --> 00:26:56,740
Some people, after taking it,

358
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:59,240
[Sis, I won't turn into someone else—
and neither will you.]

359
00:26:57,300 --> 00:26:58,620
go from being calm

360
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:01,100
to becoming irritable and short-tempered.

361
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:02,780
And others,

362
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:04,520
after taking it...

363
00:27:07,010 --> 00:27:07,700
Director Dai.

364
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:08,160
Come in.

365
00:27:08,220 --> 00:27:10,020
I'd like to ask for some time off.

366
00:27:10,870 --> 00:27:12,690
Did the school call the parents in again?

367
00:27:12,690 --> 00:27:13,140
No.

368
00:27:13,190 --> 00:27:13,830
Well,

369
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:16,490
Wang Ping and Wang An
are being released from rehab.

370
00:27:16,490 --> 00:27:18,620
I was thinking of going to pick them up.

371
00:27:18,710 --> 00:27:20,380
Their time's up—they're being released.

372
00:27:20,380 --> 00:27:21,380
Alright, go ahead.

373
00:27:21,380 --> 00:27:21,700
Okay.

374
00:27:21,700 --> 00:27:23,160
I'm giving you the day off.

375
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:24,390
You don't need to come in
tomorrow morning either—

376
00:27:24,390 --> 00:27:25,590
get some rest at home.

377
00:27:26,150 --> 00:27:27,480
I've heard everything.

378
00:27:28,590 --> 00:27:29,980
Since Ding Lai died,

379
00:27:30,630 --> 00:27:31,630
you've been doing field visits
during the day,

380
00:27:31,630 --> 00:27:32,890
reviewing surveillance at night,

381
00:27:32,890 --> 00:27:34,370
and taking care of your kids
whenever you have a moment.

382
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:36,110
I'm worried you'll drop dead
from exhaustion.

383
00:27:36,110 --> 00:27:37,300
Why would I drop dead?

384
00:27:37,300 --> 00:27:37,560
I...

385
00:27:37,580 --> 00:27:38,780
I can hold on.

386
00:27:38,910 --> 00:27:40,840
About Ding Lai getting hit by a car,

387
00:27:40,910 --> 00:27:41,910
do you really believe

388
00:27:41,910 --> 00:27:44,240
it was just an ordinary traffic accident?

389
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:48,800
Wenjing,

390
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:52,070
the last drug dealer is dead.

391
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:54,870
The drug case
has turned into a traffic case.

392
00:27:54,870 --> 00:27:57,270
Wouldn't it be better if everyone relaxed?

393
00:27:58,450 --> 00:28:00,470
Why do you always talk about backing down?

394
00:28:00,470 --> 00:28:03,260
Do you think I don't know
what's going on in your head?

395
00:28:03,260 --> 00:28:04,670
You must be worrying about

396
00:28:04,670 --> 00:28:06,020
the fact that we still have
450 grams of hallucinogen

397
00:28:06,020 --> 00:28:07,620
that haven't been found yet.

398
00:28:09,310 --> 00:28:10,570
I am worrying about it.

399
00:28:11,980 --> 00:28:13,780
But I also want to close the case.

400
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,920
Look, we've been cops for years.

401
00:28:18,590 --> 00:28:20,300
Not every case

402
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:22,610
can be perfectly
clean-cut and crystal clear,

403
00:28:22,610 --> 00:28:23,330
right?

404
00:28:24,500 --> 00:28:26,960
But sooner or later,
the truth will come out.

405
00:28:31,420 --> 00:28:32,270
Alright.

406
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:34,490
If you want to investigate,
I won't stop you.

407
00:28:34,490 --> 00:28:35,820
I just have one request:

408
00:28:37,830 --> 00:28:39,490
don't push yourself too hard.

409
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:43,260
I'm just worried that one day
I'll have to show up at your house

410
00:28:43,260 --> 00:28:45,520
and hand medals to your dad and your kids.

411
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:46,350
What are you talking about?

412
00:28:46,350 --> 00:28:47,540
Who's making you hand out medals?

413
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:48,420
You're hilarious.

414
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:49,490
You have no faith in me.

415
00:28:49,490 --> 00:28:51,210
Then take my words to heart.

416
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:51,830
I'll take that to heart…

417
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:52,980
Alright,

418
00:28:52,980 --> 00:28:54,150
it's noted.

419
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:56,210
She's so stubborn.

420
00:29:10,530 --> 00:29:11,390
Officer Zhang.

421
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:14,780
Are you looking for Wenjing again?

422
00:29:14,780 --> 00:29:16,780
Why can't I be here for you this time?

423
00:29:17,350 --> 00:29:18,670
Don't tease me.

424
00:29:18,670 --> 00:29:20,460
You said we'd have dinner
together last time,

425
00:29:20,460 --> 00:29:21,980
but it still hasn't happened.

426
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:23,910
I've just been really busy lately.

427
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:24,540
Of course,

428
00:29:24,540 --> 00:29:26,110
no matter how busy I am,
I'm never busier than you guys.

429
00:29:26,110 --> 00:29:27,860
She's so busy that I haven't even
been able to see her.

430
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:29,060
At this rate,

431
00:29:29,150 --> 00:29:30,860
she's going to get promoted, right?

432
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:32,300
I don't know if she will,

433
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:33,350
but if Wenjing becomes director,

434
00:29:33,350 --> 00:29:34,540
I'm all for it.

435
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:36,610
You're really good to our Wenjing.

436
00:29:36,610 --> 00:29:37,440
Exactly.

437
00:29:38,020 --> 00:29:39,020
Are you guys still

438
00:29:39,150 --> 00:29:40,110
working on that

439
00:29:40,830 --> 00:29:41,250
drug...

440
00:29:41,250 --> 00:29:42,580
drug trafficking case?

441
00:29:43,410 --> 00:29:44,320
Didn't you watch the news?

442
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,430
That's in the past.

443
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:46,500
There you go again,

444
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:47,870
playing "cops and civilians—
one big family."

445
00:29:47,870 --> 00:29:48,400
Wenjing,

446
00:29:48,910 --> 00:29:50,510
he said you're going to become director.

447
00:29:50,510 --> 00:29:51,590
Maybe in my next life.

448
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:52,870
Don't touch the stuff on my desk.

449
00:29:52,870 --> 00:29:54,270
I'll go through it tomorrow.

450
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:56,110
Finally, you're not bringing work
into your personal life.

451
00:29:56,110 --> 00:29:57,110
That's progress.

452
00:29:57,110 --> 00:29:57,870
You're teasing me.

453
00:29:57,870 --> 00:29:58,630
You're teasing a big shot, huh?

454
00:29:58,630 --> 00:29:59,260
Officer Zhang,

455
00:29:59,260 --> 00:30:00,340
you're looking sharp today.

456
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:01,350
I'll wait for you to ask me out to dinner.

457
00:30:01,350 --> 00:30:01,880
Wenjing,

458
00:30:02,270 --> 00:30:03,180
take my car.

459
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:05,510
Is this your car?

460
00:30:06,630 --> 00:30:08,090
Isn't this the one you've always liked?

461
00:30:08,090 --> 00:30:08,680
You got it!

462
00:30:08,680 --> 00:30:10,600
I picked up a new model recently.

463
00:30:10,910 --> 00:30:12,180
If you make money, you've gotta spend it.

464
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:12,750
Get in.

465
00:30:13,300 --> 00:30:14,520
You're looking sharp.

466
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,280
Xiaoya.

467
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:18,210
The new car smell.

468
00:30:18,210 --> 00:30:19,370
Take it in.

469
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:22,680
[Xiekang Drug Rehabilitation Center]

470
00:30:20,350 --> 00:30:23,060
The yellow-level monitoring
will last at least three years.

471
00:30:23,060 --> 00:30:24,120
During these three years,

472
00:30:24,120 --> 00:30:27,320
you must report to
the designated department regularly.

473
00:30:27,500 --> 00:30:29,240
The monitoring system is nationwide—

474
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:32,330
using your ID

475
00:30:32,350 --> 00:30:33,850
for trains, flights, hotels,
or internet access

476
00:30:33,850 --> 00:30:35,240
will trigger an alert.

477
00:30:35,580 --> 00:30:38,110
You also have to undergo inspections
by public security authorities.

478
00:30:38,110 --> 00:30:39,180
After three years,

479
00:30:39,330 --> 00:30:41,100
if it's verified
that you haven't relapsed,

480
00:30:41,100 --> 00:30:43,750
you can request a certificate
from the local police station.

481
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:46,650
Then the city Public Security Bureau
can lift the dynamic monitoring,

482
00:30:46,650 --> 00:30:48,360
lowering your status from yellow

483
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:50,080
to blue,

484
00:30:50,660 --> 00:30:53,530
and eventually remove the ID alert.

485
00:30:54,500 --> 00:30:56,960
Can I still
take the graduate entrance exam?

486
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:59,200
Theoretically, it won't affect it.

487
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:00,550
Theoretically?

488
00:31:01,100 --> 00:31:03,070
People with a history of drug use
cannot join the military

489
00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:05,080
or work in state-owned enterprises,

490
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,940
but for enrollment, employment,

491
00:31:07,190 --> 00:31:08,810
and social security benefits,

492
00:31:08,810 --> 00:31:10,760
there is no official discrimination.

493
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:13,030
So, will the people in charge of
the grad school political review

494
00:31:13,030 --> 00:31:14,830
know I've been to rehab?

495
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,250
Yes.

496
00:31:20,690 --> 00:31:22,350
Take this up to the second floor, sign,

497
00:31:22,350 --> 00:31:24,550
and collect your personal belongings.

498
00:31:41,910 --> 00:31:42,830
What did Mr. Qi say about

499
00:31:42,830 --> 00:31:44,150
the grad exam?

500
00:31:44,630 --> 00:31:45,310
It's okay.

501
00:31:45,700 --> 00:31:46,900
It won't be affected.

502
00:31:47,930 --> 00:31:49,140
Isn't that great?

503
00:31:51,940 --> 00:31:52,660
Thank you.

504
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:54,970
They're both waiting outside.

505
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,280
This is a fresh start.

506
00:32:01,350 --> 00:32:02,020
From now on,

507
00:32:02,050 --> 00:32:03,850
stop dragging your sister down.

508
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,600
After the dealer nicknamed Quan

509
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:09,710
died,

510
00:32:09,730 --> 00:32:11,450
we interrogated his subordinate.

511
00:32:11,450 --> 00:32:13,120
The subordinate admitted
that he had pressured

512
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:14,650
Tang Sile into using drugs.

513
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:18,240
Tang Sile never even
intended to commit suicide.

514
00:32:18,390 --> 00:32:19,760
During the chase,

515
00:32:19,790 --> 00:32:21,090
he realized he couldn't leave

516
00:32:21,090 --> 00:32:22,460
any evidence against me,
so he tried to destroy it all.

517
00:32:22,460 --> 00:32:23,180
He ran out of options

518
00:32:23,180 --> 00:32:24,330
and swallowed all the drugs.

519
00:32:24,330 --> 00:32:25,200
Otherwise,

520
00:32:26,330 --> 00:32:27,440
at such a young age,

521
00:32:27,470 --> 00:32:28,670
with a bright future ahead...

522
00:32:28,670 --> 00:32:30,430
Look at what this drug

523
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,680
has done to people.

524
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:34,450
Wang An, you need to
have some sense of the consequences.

525
00:32:34,450 --> 00:32:35,840
If your sister hadn't found out in time,

526
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,640
just imagine the consequences.

527
00:32:40,720 --> 00:32:41,570
I understand.

528
00:32:43,080 --> 00:32:44,350
I know I was wrong,

529
00:32:44,380 --> 00:32:45,510
and I hurt my sister.

530
00:32:46,610 --> 00:32:47,870
I apologize to you all.

531
00:32:47,980 --> 00:32:48,670
That's enough.

532
00:32:48,670 --> 00:32:50,010
Why say that?

533
00:32:51,890 --> 00:32:52,910
You were fooled

534
00:32:52,910 --> 00:32:54,190
by Tang Sile too,

535
00:32:54,190 --> 00:32:54,920
weren't you?

536
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:00,920
Wenjing, go on.

537
00:33:01,670 --> 00:33:02,780
I heard that several dealers

538
00:33:02,780 --> 00:33:04,300
in the county died.

539
00:33:04,330 --> 00:33:05,440
You just mentioned Quan—

540
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:07,050
did he have a boss behind him?

541
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:08,350
Is the boss still alive?

542
00:33:08,350 --> 00:33:09,610
Why are you so excited?

543
00:33:09,620 --> 00:33:11,680
Why are you so interested in our case?

544
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:13,300
Isn't it thrilling?

545
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:15,840
Besides, I love suspense stories.

546
00:33:16,710 --> 00:33:17,870
In a couple of days,
we have a Wechat business meetup—

547
00:33:17,870 --> 00:33:19,360
I'll just go over and brag a little.

548
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:20,090
I've told you

549
00:33:20,110 --> 00:33:21,570
everything I can tell you.

550
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:22,510
As for what I can't say,

551
00:33:22,510 --> 00:33:23,950
I'm not allowed to.

552
00:33:23,980 --> 00:33:24,780
Do you think I'd still have my job

553
00:33:24,780 --> 00:33:26,150
if I told you everything?

554
00:33:26,150 --> 00:33:26,830
Fine.

555
00:33:27,150 --> 00:33:28,340
If you can talk about it later,

556
00:33:28,340 --> 00:33:29,380
tell me then.

557
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:30,480
Sure.

558
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:31,950
Wenjing,

559
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:35,680
are there still drug dealers
in our county?

560
00:33:36,530 --> 00:33:37,290
I don't know.

561
00:33:43,150 --> 00:33:44,310
Xiaoya, stop here.

562
00:33:45,020 --> 00:33:45,590
Okay.

563
00:33:46,290 --> 00:33:47,570
Sorry for the trouble.

564
00:33:47,850 --> 00:33:48,710
Don't say that.

565
00:33:48,710 --> 00:33:49,510
You can go now.

566
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:50,550
Take care, you two.

567
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:51,120
Okay.

568
00:33:52,490 --> 00:33:53,620
We'll keep in touch.

569
00:34:06,430 --> 00:34:07,760
Don't you think

570
00:34:08,290 --> 00:34:10,120
there's something off about them?

571
00:34:10,120 --> 00:34:10,960
I do.

572
00:34:17,710 --> 00:34:18,239
Let's go.

573
00:34:22,389 --> 00:34:26,610
[Nuanfeng County People's Hospital]

574
00:34:37,270 --> 00:34:37,940
Thank you.

575
00:34:40,239 --> 00:34:41,199
You're in this room.

576
00:34:41,199 --> 00:34:43,600
I've been going up and down
several floors.

577
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:46,070
The director heard I was injured on duty

578
00:34:46,070 --> 00:34:48,060
and insisted I stay
in the special care unit.

579
00:34:48,060 --> 00:34:49,750
But the whole hospital
only has one unit like this

580
00:34:49,750 --> 00:34:50,739
and they arranged me here.

581
00:34:50,739 --> 00:34:51,280
It's great.

582
00:34:51,280 --> 00:34:52,540
What great treatment.

583
00:34:52,710 --> 00:34:53,540
I refused,

584
00:34:53,580 --> 00:34:54,639
but they insisted.

585
00:34:54,659 --> 00:34:55,469
Come on.

586
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:57,270
He meant well.

587
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,400
It's nice here.

588
00:34:58,430 --> 00:34:59,090
It's quiet.

589
00:34:59,370 --> 00:34:59,870
Let me see.

590
00:34:59,870 --> 00:35:00,720
Let me check your wound.

591
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:01,920
How's your recovery?

592
00:35:03,530 --> 00:35:04,720
There's nothing to look at.

593
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:05,320
It's fine.

594
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:08,460
When I got injured at the police academy,

595
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:09,830
you were a kid.

596
00:35:09,830 --> 00:35:11,130
Can't I just take a look?

597
00:35:11,130 --> 00:35:12,190
You're like my son.

598
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:13,270
My son pushes me out

599
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:14,350
at bath time

600
00:35:14,350 --> 00:35:15,910
and won't let me in.

601
00:35:16,650 --> 00:35:17,210
Come on.

602
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,770
Have something good to eat.

603
00:35:19,900 --> 00:35:20,900
Can you sit up?

604
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:21,800
Yes.

605
00:35:22,850 --> 00:35:24,580
I brought some braised dishes.

606
00:35:24,620 --> 00:35:25,750
It's delicious.

607
00:35:25,750 --> 00:35:27,080
I had to line up for this;

608
00:35:27,540 --> 00:35:29,140
it stays fresh for 48 hours—

609
00:35:29,140 --> 00:35:29,780
two days.

610
00:35:49,450 --> 00:35:51,040
I'm your lifesaver, after all.

611
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,160
I even brought you food.

612
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:53,830
Could you be a bit more enthusiastic?

613
00:35:53,830 --> 00:35:54,650
I paid for this.

614
00:35:54,650 --> 00:35:56,170
It wasn't cheap.

615
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:58,450
Back then...

616
00:35:58,460 --> 00:35:59,790
I should've gone after Ding Lai.

617
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:01,020
You've said that several times.

618
00:36:01,020 --> 00:36:01,830
If I had gone after Ding Lai,

619
00:36:01,830 --> 00:36:03,320
would you even be eating this now?

620
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:05,300
You'd be dead by now,

621
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:06,070
buddy.

622
00:36:06,460 --> 00:36:07,310
Now Ding Lai is dead,

623
00:36:07,310 --> 00:36:07,860
and you're alive.

624
00:36:07,860 --> 00:36:09,660
What are you not satisfied with?

625
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,840
I'm not mad at you.

626
00:36:16,390 --> 00:36:18,390
I'm mad at myself for being useless.

627
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,500
Ding Lai died senselessly.

628
00:36:20,500 --> 00:36:22,620
Lv Deli's goods still
haven't been recovered.

629
00:36:22,620 --> 00:36:24,520
My brother's case
still hasn't been solved.

630
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:25,880
Aren't you dissatisfied too?

631
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:28,510
Cases have to be solved step by step.

632
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:30,100
No rule says that

633
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:31,020
just because you want to solve a case,

634
00:36:31,020 --> 00:36:33,080
you can solve it immediately, right?

635
00:36:38,870 --> 00:36:40,130
Is there any progress?

636
00:36:42,750 --> 00:36:44,270
Sort of but not really.

637
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:45,830
The truck that ran over Ding Lai

638
00:36:45,830 --> 00:36:47,460
was a single-cabin lorry

639
00:36:47,810 --> 00:36:48,580
with a fake license plate—

640
00:36:48,580 --> 00:36:50,030
there's no way to trace it.

641
00:36:50,030 --> 00:36:52,630
The motorcycle Ding Lai
was riding was stolen.

642
00:36:53,470 --> 00:36:55,230
The original owner was located,

643
00:36:55,230 --> 00:36:56,120
but there was no issue—

644
00:36:56,120 --> 00:36:57,520
he just lost it.

645
00:36:58,180 --> 00:36:59,830
In addition, Ding Lai

646
00:36:59,830 --> 00:37:00,830
was wearing a delivery uniform.

647
00:37:00,830 --> 00:37:01,870
Based on the material

648
00:37:01,870 --> 00:37:03,270
and style, we were able to

649
00:37:03,300 --> 00:37:04,760
locate the shop on Taobao.

650
00:37:04,870 --> 00:37:06,760
The shop owner provided a contact number

651
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,350
for the courier
who had delivered the items.

652
00:37:08,350 --> 00:37:09,350
The courier had left the package

653
00:37:09,350 --> 00:37:10,770
within one kilometer

654
00:37:10,790 --> 00:37:12,270
of the stolen motorcycle,

655
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:14,230
at the entrance of a building unit.

656
00:37:14,390 --> 00:37:15,180
The note instructed him

657
00:37:15,180 --> 00:37:16,770
to "leave it at the unit entrance and go,"

658
00:37:16,770 --> 00:37:18,440
which he followed exactly.

659
00:37:19,180 --> 00:37:20,790
So far, this is
all the information we have.

660
00:37:20,790 --> 00:37:22,870
It provides some leads,
but not significant ones.

661
00:37:22,870 --> 00:37:25,270
His hiding place is likely nearby.

662
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:26,620
That's what I thought, too.

663
00:37:26,620 --> 00:37:28,580
But the direction Ding Lai fled that day

664
00:37:28,580 --> 00:37:30,460
is different from this address,

665
00:37:31,370 --> 00:37:33,230
so there's no way to connect them.

666
00:37:34,690 --> 00:37:36,350
What about the payment account?
Was it investigated?

667
00:37:36,350 --> 00:37:37,540
The Taobao account,

668
00:37:37,540 --> 00:37:38,310
phone account,

669
00:37:38,310 --> 00:37:39,240
and bank account

670
00:37:39,710 --> 00:37:41,540
all belong to a villager from Zaodao Town.

671
00:37:41,540 --> 00:37:43,140
This was set up years ago

672
00:37:43,180 --> 00:37:44,500
when Ding Lai was involved in fraud,

673
00:37:44,500 --> 00:37:45,750
and he has been using

674
00:37:45,750 --> 00:37:47,010
the same ID ever since.

675
00:37:48,950 --> 00:37:51,080
You have to admit, he's quite cunning.

676
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:54,000
He's always one step ahead of us,

677
00:37:54,030 --> 00:37:55,070
just a bit faster.

678
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,320
What about the phone?

679
00:37:57,620 --> 00:37:58,480
Did you find it?

680
00:37:59,100 --> 00:37:59,640
No.

681
00:38:03,270 --> 00:38:04,620
He has a secure phone.

682
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:06,580
Didn't he carry it when he went out?

683
00:38:09,230 --> 00:38:12,360
For Ding Lai to hide in Nuanfeng County
for a whole month,

684
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:13,190
he must either

685
00:38:13,260 --> 00:38:15,140
have a prearranged safe house

686
00:38:15,270 --> 00:38:16,580
or accomplices.

687
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,790
Otherwise, even basic things
like getting meals would be a problem.

688
00:38:18,790 --> 00:38:20,710
I'm convinced he must have accomplices,

689
00:38:20,710 --> 00:38:22,840
so that's the direction I'm pursuing.

690
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:24,730
Do you think

691
00:38:26,770 --> 00:38:28,910
the person
who took the girl from the hotel

692
00:38:28,910 --> 00:38:30,770
is one of Ding Lai's accomplices?

693
00:38:34,310 --> 00:38:35,310
Longzheng,

694
00:38:35,620 --> 00:38:36,790
can you tell me another story

695
00:38:36,790 --> 00:38:38,350
about catching bad guys?

696
00:38:38,380 --> 00:38:38,750
Sure.

697
00:38:38,830 --> 00:38:39,610
Let me finish eating first.

698
00:38:39,610 --> 00:38:40,350
Let me finish eating first.

699
00:38:40,350 --> 00:38:41,210
Sit over there.

700
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:42,500
Who's this?

701
00:38:42,870 --> 00:38:43,780
Someone from the ward over there.

702
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:44,770
Did you brag about something?

703
00:38:44,770 --> 00:38:45,920
What bragging?

704
00:38:46,290 --> 00:38:47,600
I'm Xue Jiang.

705
00:38:48,040 --> 00:38:49,290
Once I recover,

706
00:38:49,530 --> 00:38:51,530
I want to be a police officer

707
00:38:51,870 --> 00:38:52,830
like Longzheng,

708
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:54,650
protecting the innocent.

709
00:38:54,950 --> 00:38:56,230
And you say you weren't bragging?

710
00:38:56,230 --> 00:38:57,390
I wasn't.

711
00:38:57,720 --> 00:38:59,020
-Auntie,
-Jin Longzheng...

712
00:38:59,020 --> 00:39:00,180
are you a police officer too?

713
00:39:00,180 --> 00:39:00,660
I am.

714
00:39:00,660 --> 00:39:01,540
But I'm not as brave as he is.

715
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:02,540
See, he got injured,

716
00:39:02,540 --> 00:39:03,740
and I'm perfectly fine.

717
00:39:03,740 --> 00:39:04,910
That's a great dream you have.

718
00:39:04,910 --> 00:39:06,020
Here, have some pork head meat.

719
00:39:06,020 --> 00:39:07,350
Try it, it's delicious.

720
00:39:07,470 --> 00:39:10,240
I just want to listen to
Longzheng's stories.

721
00:39:10,980 --> 00:39:12,320
So he's just here for the stories.

722
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:12,870
Hurry up and eat.

723
00:39:12,870 --> 00:39:14,870
Finish up so you can tell him a story.

724
00:39:31,390 --> 00:39:32,720
What are you doing here?

725
00:39:34,880 --> 00:39:36,280
I still want

726
00:39:37,220 --> 00:39:38,580
to speak my mind.

727
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:40,240
If you have something to say,

728
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,080
just say it.

729
00:39:44,450 --> 00:39:46,740
Jiang was born with a heart defect.

730
00:39:48,150 --> 00:39:51,060
Jiajia has been suffering from
uremia for several years.

731
00:39:51,060 --> 00:39:52,620
We're both fathers,

732
00:39:54,260 --> 00:39:55,580
all fighting desperately

733
00:39:55,580 --> 00:39:57,200
to keep our children alive.

734
00:39:59,870 --> 00:40:01,350
I know you've surely

735
00:40:01,820 --> 00:40:04,570
experienced many times when you saw hope

736
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:06,170
only for it to be dashed.

737
00:40:13,390 --> 00:40:14,270
A few years ago,

738
00:40:15,890 --> 00:40:17,960
my parents and my wife

739
00:40:20,310 --> 00:40:21,840
were killed in an accident.

740
00:40:28,690 --> 00:40:29,950
Now, aside from my daughter,

741
00:40:29,950 --> 00:40:31,100
I have nothing left.

742
00:40:32,770 --> 00:40:34,510
I don't know how to keep going.

743
00:40:39,170 --> 00:40:41,240
What does that have to do with me?

744
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:46,020
My son is getting better.

745
00:40:46,020 --> 00:40:46,850
Can't you see?

746
00:40:56,610 --> 00:40:58,280
Can you give me a little hope?

747
00:41:03,130 --> 00:41:03,850
Give what?

748
00:41:04,190 --> 00:41:04,920
How?

749
00:41:04,950 --> 00:41:05,670
With what?

750
00:41:07,870 --> 00:41:09,870
I just want to hear you say one thing:

751
00:41:13,820 --> 00:41:14,700
if

752
00:41:16,500 --> 00:41:17,350
Jiang

753
00:41:18,500 --> 00:41:20,190
doesn't make it,

754
00:41:20,210 --> 00:41:21,810
could you consider Jiajia?

755
00:41:22,390 --> 00:41:25,120
I'll have Jiajia take care of
you when you get old.

756
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,550
Haven't I told you?

757
00:41:27,870 --> 00:41:29,400
Stop thinking about my son.

758
00:41:29,590 --> 00:41:30,990
I'll say it one more time:

759
00:41:31,060 --> 00:41:32,350
if you keep thinking about my son,

760
00:41:32,350 --> 00:41:33,440
I'll risk my life

761
00:41:33,470 --> 00:41:35,270
to kill you. Do you believe that?

762
00:41:38,290 --> 00:41:39,850
I just want a word from you.

763
00:41:42,060 --> 00:41:43,580
Lie to me if you have to.

764
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:48,370
Give me something to live for.

765
00:42:06,220 --> 00:42:06,970
I can't.

766
00:42:07,860 --> 00:42:08,990
Not even half a word.

767
00:42:19,940 --> 00:42:21,190
I know you need money.

768
00:42:23,060 --> 00:42:23,870
I can pay.

769
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:26,900
I can give you whatever amount you want.

770
00:42:28,180 --> 00:42:28,980
No matter how poor I am,

771
00:42:28,980 --> 00:42:30,620
I won't sell my son's organs.

772
00:42:30,980 --> 00:42:32,440
I'm not asking you to sell.

773
00:42:32,990 --> 00:42:33,760
I...

774
00:42:34,910 --> 00:42:36,230
Just name a figure.

775
00:42:37,540 --> 00:42:39,140
I can leave the money here

776
00:42:39,140 --> 00:42:40,070
with you for now.

777
00:42:40,580 --> 00:42:42,110
If he gets better,

778
00:42:42,130 --> 00:42:43,770
you won't have to give it back.

779
00:42:43,770 --> 00:42:45,020
Consider it my contribution

780
00:42:45,020 --> 00:42:46,670
to his future education.

781
00:42:49,240 --> 00:42:50,120
But if...

782
00:42:50,140 --> 00:42:51,220
Are you crazy?

783
00:42:52,500 --> 00:42:53,230
Just bored with nothing to do?

784
00:42:53,230 --> 00:42:55,090
Got money and nowhere to spend it?

785
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:58,560
Fine.

786
00:42:59,580 --> 00:43:00,830
If you've got money
and nowhere to spend it, give it to me.

787
00:43:00,830 --> 00:43:01,830
One million yuan.

788
00:43:01,980 --> 00:43:02,580
Bring it here.

789
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:03,380
Do you have it?

790
00:43:05,390 --> 00:43:06,910
After all these years of
paying for your child's treatment,

791
00:43:06,910 --> 00:43:07,950
don't you know how much you've got left?

792
00:43:07,950 --> 00:43:08,810
One million yuan?

793
00:43:08,810 --> 00:43:09,990
Yes, one million yuan.

794
00:43:09,990 --> 00:43:10,840
Bring it here.

795
00:43:15,070 --> 00:43:16,070
One million yuan.

796
00:43:18,010 --> 00:43:18,820
It's settled.

797
00:44:33,710 --> 00:44:34,540
Come on.

798
00:44:34,860 --> 00:44:36,150
Don't think that doing me a favor

799
00:44:36,150 --> 00:44:37,530
gives you the right to act so boldly.

800
00:44:37,530 --> 00:44:39,260
You said it was unconditional.

801
00:44:40,540 --> 00:44:41,460
Did you find out

802
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:45,320
how Ding Lai died?

803
00:44:45,540 --> 00:44:46,870
What did the police say?

804
00:44:47,310 --> 00:44:48,840
Whenever the case comes up,

805
00:44:48,950 --> 00:44:50,140
they were vague.

806
00:44:50,710 --> 00:44:52,770
But that colleague of Hu Wenjing said

807
00:44:52,940 --> 00:44:53,870
the drug dealers

808
00:44:55,100 --> 00:44:56,830
are already a thing of the past.

809
00:44:57,250 --> 00:44:59,650
That should mean
the case is closed, right?

810
00:45:00,750 --> 00:45:01,540
Impossible.

811
00:45:02,220 --> 00:45:03,700
It's not that simple.

812
00:45:05,180 --> 00:45:05,960
Enough.

813
00:45:05,980 --> 00:45:07,640
I can't be bothered with all this.

814
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:09,970
Right now, the most important thing for me

815
00:45:10,620 --> 00:45:11,880
is to enjoy the moment.

816
00:45:14,750 --> 00:45:16,680
How much have you spent this month?

817
00:45:17,020 --> 00:45:18,620
Just a few hundred thousand.

818
00:45:19,060 --> 00:45:21,260
Ding Lai gave you
a little over a million in total.

819
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:23,790
At this rate, you'll
spend it all in a few days.

820
00:45:24,180 --> 00:45:26,300
Can you think about the future?

821
00:45:27,860 --> 00:45:29,720
I've already thought it through.

822
00:45:29,870 --> 00:45:31,730
I've set my eyes on an
excellent product line,

823
00:45:31,730 --> 00:45:33,600
and I want to
secure its distribution rights.

824
00:45:33,600 --> 00:45:34,440
This product

825
00:45:34,460 --> 00:45:35,990
is going to sell like crazy.

826
00:45:36,350 --> 00:45:37,140
Then

827
00:45:37,140 --> 00:45:39,000
everyone in Haizhou City will see

828
00:45:39,130 --> 00:45:41,860
who the best microbusiness owner
here really is.

829
00:45:43,230 --> 00:45:44,460
Fame brings trouble.

830
00:45:44,860 --> 00:45:46,900
Business isn't that easy.

831
00:46:10,180 --> 00:46:11,490
Actually, lately,

832
00:46:11,670 --> 00:46:13,930
I've been looking at you more favorably.

833
00:46:15,450 --> 00:46:16,530
You're

834
00:46:16,550 --> 00:46:17,880
actually quite nice.

835
00:46:18,850 --> 00:46:19,850
But you're

836
00:46:21,180 --> 00:46:22,710
just a little too cautious.

837
00:46:23,760 --> 00:46:25,760
Do you remember what I just told you?

838
00:46:28,540 --> 00:46:30,540
You have to enjoy life while you can.

839
00:47:00,330 --> 00:47:02,710
[Nuanfeng; Drug]

840
00:47:02,820 --> 00:47:06,720
[Haizhou Police Crack Major Drug Trafficking Case,
Successfully Dismantle Local Drug Network]

841
00:47:22,750 --> 00:47:30,320
[Next Episode Preview]
